          h2 Stephen Schaapveld &mdash; Psychologist
          h3 Background
          p I am a New Zealand trained and registered Psychologist who works with men and women of all ages, backgrounds and beliefs.
          p I work with you in a collaborative goal focused manner utilising a variety of therapeutic approaches to help you gain mastery and peace with the issues you are facing in your life.
          p Our sessions will help you gain a deeper insight into what is causing you to feel and act the way you do and to gain coping skills and strategies to manage the difficulties you are experiencing so you can have a more rewarding and fulfilling life.
          h3 Qualifications
          ul 
            li Post Graduate Diploma in Health Psychology - (The University of Auckland)
            li Master of Science in Health Psychology – First class honours (The University of Auckland)
            li Bachelor of Science – (The University of Auckland)
            li NZ Registered Psychologist
            li Member of NZ Psychological Society 
          h3 Therapy Approach
          p Therapies I use include Cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT), Mindfulness, Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT), Compassion Focused Therapy (CFT) and Solution Focused Therapy (SFT). I work through the sessions with you at your pace in order for you to get the absolute most out of the time we spend together.
          p I see people who often present with issues such as:
          ul
            li Low and Depressed Mood
            li Stress
            li Worry and Anxiety
            li Motivational Problems
            li Medically Unexplained Symptoms
            li Men’s issues 
            li Spirituality or Existential Issues
            li Chronic Pain
            li The challenges and struggles of everyday life
